IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE PROVISION OF RESIDENTIAL SUPPORT SERVICES, INCLUDING CASE MANAGEMENT, TO THE MENTALLY ILL AND DEVELOPMENTALLY DISABLED INDIVIDUALS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES ELDERLY OR DISABLED PERSONS WITH HOUSING FACILITIES AND SERVICES SPECIALLY DESIGNED TO MEET THEIR PHYSICAL, SOCIAL, AND PSYCHOLOGICAL NEEDS, AND TO PROMOTE THEIR HEALTH, SECURITY, HAPPINESS AND USEFULNESS IN LONGER LIVING.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDED HOUSING AND LIVING ASSISTANCE TO DISABLED PERSONS.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION WAS PREVIOUSLY INCLUDED AS A SUBORDINATE IN A GROUP RETURN FILING WITH THE CONNECTICUT INSTITUTE OF THE BLIND, INC. DURING FISCAL YEAR 2018, THE ORGANIZATION BEGAN FILING A SEPARATE RETURN. AS A RESULT, THE ORGANIZATION IS CONSIDERED TO BE IN YEAR 5 OF ITS FIRST 5 YEARS AS A 501(C)(3).

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PATTI WALKER RECEIVED A $55,000 PAYMENT INTO HER 457(F) PLAN DURING THE 2021 CALENDAR YEAR. PATTI, JAMES, MONICA, DETRIE, GRETHCHEN, DAVID, DEBORAH AND ANGELA EACH RECEIVED $10,000 PAYMENTS INTO THEIR 457(B) PLANS DURING THE 2021 CALENDAR YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DEMARCO MANAGMENT CORPORATION, A PROPERTY MANAGEMENT COMPANY IS UTILIZED TO OPERATE THE FACILITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NO COMMITTEE HAS THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COPY OF THE 990 WAS EMAILED TO THE BOARD PRIOR TO THE RETURN BEING FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AGENCY REQUIRES THAT ALL EMPLOYEES UPON HIRE ACKNOWLEDGE THAT THEY HAVE RECEIVED AND UNDERSTAND THE AGENCY'S POLICY ON CORPORATE COMPLIANCE, ETHICS, AND CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AS OUTLINED IN THE EMPLOYEE HANDBOOK. ANNUALLY, THE AGENCY REQUIRES ALL STAFF TO COMPLETE A COMPETENCY-BASED TRAINING ON ETHICS AND COMPLIANCE WHICH ALSO INCLUDES CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. BOARD MEMBERS ARE ALSO REQUIRED TO SIGN A NO CONFLICT STATEMENT WHILE TENURED WITH THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A SALARY STUDY IS PERFORMED AND IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AND THROUGH THE STATE OF CONNECTICUT.
